<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:scilab="http://www.scilab.org" xml:lang="en" xml:id="rmfield">
    <refnamediv>
        <refname>rmfield</refname>
        <refpurpose>Remove fields from a struct</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>
    <refsynopsisdiv>
        <title>Syntax</title>
        <synopsis>stout = rmfield(stin, fields)</synopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>
    <refsection>
        <title>Arguments</title>
        <variablelist>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>stin</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>A struct variable.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>fields</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>String matrix or cell of strings, the names of the fields to remove.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>stout</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>A struct variable having the same dimensions as <literal>stin</literal> from which some fields have be removed.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
    </refsection>
    <refsection>
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>
            The <function>rmfield</function> function removes fields from a struct but without modifying its dimensions.
            If <literal>fields</literal> is an empty matrix or an empty cell, then <literal>stin</literal> and <literal>stout</literal> are the same.
        </para>
    </refsection>
    <refsection>
        <title>Examples</title>
        <programlisting role="example">
            st = struct("a", 1, "b", 2, "c", 3, "d", 4)
            s2 = rmfield(st, []) // No fields will be removed
            s1 = rmfield(st, "a")
            s3 = rmfield(st, {"b", "c"})
            s4 = rmfield(st, {"b", "c"; "d", "a"}) // All fields will be removed
        </programlisting>
    </refsection>
